            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>While the macaroni is cooking, melt 15g <span class=\"text-purple\">[25g]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[30g]</span> <strong>butter</strong> in the reserved pan over a medium heat</p><p>Once melted, add the <strong>sliced leek</strong>, <strong>chopped garlic</strong>, <strong>half </strong>your <strong>ground smoked paprika </strong>(you'll use the rest later!) and a pinch of <strong>salt</strong> and cook for 3-4 min until softened</p><p>Once softened, add 15g <span class=\"text-purple\">[25g]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[30g]</span> <strong>flour</strong> and stir with a wooden spoon for 1-2 min or until a sandy paste coats the leek – this is your <strong>leek roux</strong></p>",
      "order": 4,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-4-1670329809419-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
